extends layout

block content
  .container
    .row.page-header
      .col-lg-12.text-center
        h1(style="color: white;") Welcome to the World of Mechanical Engineering
        p Explore the World of Mechanical Engineering

      .col-lg-6.text-center
        img(src="https://armiet.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/B1P1.jpeg", alt="Mechanical Engineering Illustration", style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;")

    .row.about-mechanical-engineering
      .col-lg-6
        h2(style="color: white;") What is Mechanical Engineering?
        p.large-font
          | Mechanical Engineering is a diverse field that involves the design, development, and maintenance of mechanical systems and devices. Mechanical engineers work on a wide range of projects, from designing machinery and equipment to optimizing manufacturing processes.

    .row.job-opportunities
      .col-lg-12
        h2(style="color: white;") Career Opportunities in Mechanical Engineering
        p.large-font
          | The field of Mechanical Engineering offers a plethora of exciting career opportunities. Here are some prominent job roles in the field:
        ul
          li Mechanical Design Engineer: Create and optimize mechanical systems and products.
          li Aerospace Engineer: Work on aircraft and spacecraft design and development.
          li Manufacturing Engineer: Improve production processes and quality control.
          li HVAC Engineer: Design heating, ventilation, and air conditioning systems.
          li Automotive Engineer: Focus on the automotive industry, designing vehicles and components.
          li Robotics Engineer: Develop robotic systems for various applications.

        p.large-font
          | Whether you're interested in robotics, aerospace, or manufacturing, a career in Mechanical Engineering can lead to diverse and rewarding roles.

    .row.future-of-mechanical-engineering
      .col-lg-12
        h2(style="color: white;") The Future of Mechanical Engineering
        p.large-font
          | The field of Mechanical Engineering is constantly evolving with advancements in technology and innovation. Here are some exciting trends shaping the future of Mechanical Engineering:

        ul
          li Smart Manufacturing: Integration of IoT and automation in manufacturing processes.
          li Sustainable Design: Emphasis on eco-friendly and energy-efficient solutions.
          li 3D Printing: Revolutionizing prototyping and manufacturing.
          li Artificial Intelligence: AI-driven design and optimization of mechanical systems.
          li Renewable Energy: Developing sustainable energy solutions.

        p.large-font
          | As technology continues to advance, Mechanical Engineers will play a crucial role in solving complex global challenges and creating a more sustainable future.

    .row.how-to-start
      .col-lg-12
        h2(style="color: white;") How to Start Your Career in Mechanical Engineering
        p.large-font
          | If you're passionate about Mechanical Engineering, here are some steps to kickstart your career:

        ol
          li Earn a Bachelor's Degree in Mechanical Engineering or a related field.
          li Gain hands-on experience through internships and co-op programs.
          li Build a strong foundation in mathematics and physics.
          li Stay updated with industry trends and technologies.
          li Consider pursuing advanced degrees or certifications for specialization.

    .row.explore-more
      .col-lg-12.text-center
        h2(style="color: white;") Explore More
        p.large-font
          | Ready to delve deeper into the world of Mechanical Engineering? Check out these resources:

        a(href='/courses/mechanical-engineering', class='btn btn-primary btn-lg') Explore Courses
        a(href='/blogs/mechanical-engineering', class='btn btn-secondary btn-lg') Read Blogs


